HEADWORD: Jeunesse dore
<hw>Jeu`nesse" do`r⟦eacute⟧e"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[F.]</ety>
<def>Lit., gilded youth; young people of wealth and fashion, esp. if
given to prodigal living; -- in the French Revolution, applied to young
men of the upper classes who aided in suppressing the Jacobins after the
Reign of Terror.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jew</ent>⟦br⟧
